            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I basically didn't add any extra error handling at the initial implementation, but I handled the `pos` that is exactly one position beyond the buffer because our `range` is described as \"end-exclusive.\" Therefore, such an `end_pos` combined with a `start_pos` can represent a range to the end of the buffer, which should be seen as valid and does not throw errors.\r\n\r\nIIRC, although `extmark` is also described as `end-exclusive` too, it doesn't seem to support this syntax. For an `end_row` and `end_col` pair where the `end_col` exceeds the buffer by one position, it throws an out-of-bounds index error.",
            "created_at": "2026-04-26T12:08:50Z",
